486    /**
487     * Scope a query to only include users with unique usernames
488     *
489     * @param Builder  $query
490     * @param string   $username
491     * @param int|null $excludeId
492     *
493     * @return Builder
494     */
495    public function scopeUniqueUsername($query, $username, $excludeId = NULL)
496    {
497        $query = $query->where('username', $username);
498
499        if ($excludeId) {
500            $query->where('id', '!=', $excludeId);
501        }
502
503        return $query;
504    }

660    /**
661     * Calculate profile completion percentage
662     */
663    public function getProfileCompletion(): array
664    {
665        $fields = [
666            'name'               => ! empty($this->name),
667            'surname'            => ! empty($this->surname),
668            'phone'              => ! empty($this->phone),
669            'bio'                => ! empty($this->bio),
670            'profile_picture'    => ! empty($this->profile_picture),
671            'timezone'           => ! empty($this->timezone),
672            'language'           => ! empty($this->language),
673            'two_factor_enabled' => $this->two_factor_enabled ?? FALSE,
674        ];
675
676        $completedFields = array_filter($fields);
677        $completionPercentage = round((count($completedFields) / count($fields)) * 100);
678
679        // Determine completion status
680        $status = 'incomplete';
681        if ($completionPercentage >= 90) {
682            $status = 'excellent';
683        } elseif ($completionPercentage >= 75) {
684            $status = 'good';
685        } elseif ($completionPercentage >= 50) {
686            $status = 'fair';
687        }
688
689        return [
690            'percentage'       => $completionPercentage,
691            'status'           => $status,
692            'completed_fields' => $completedFields,
693            'missing_fields'   => array_keys(array_filter($fields, fn (bool $value): bool => ! $value)),
694            'total_fields'     => count($fields),
695            'completed_count'  => count($completedFields),
696            'is_complete'      => $completionPercentage >= 90,
697        ];
698    }
699
700    /**
701     * Get profile picture URL or initials
702     */
703    public function getProfileDisplay(): array
704    {
705        $initials = strtoupper(substr($this->name, 0, 1) . substr($this->surname ?? '', 0, 1));
706
707        // Handle profile picture URL - check if it already contains full URL
708        $pictureUrl = NULL;
709        if ($this->profile_picture) {
710            if (str_starts_with($this->profile_picture, 'http')) {
711                // Already a full URL (from new upload system)
712                $pictureUrl = $this->profile_picture;
713            } else {
714                // Legacy format - add asset path
715                $pictureUrl = asset('storage/' . $this->profile_picture);
716            }
717        }
718
719        return [
720            'picture_url'  => $pictureUrl,
721            'initials'     => $initials,
722            'has_picture'  => ! empty($this->profile_picture),
723            'full_name'    => $this->full_name,
724            'display_name' => ($this->full_name ?: $this->username) ?: $this->email,
725            'bio'          => $this->bio,
726            'timezone'     => $this->timezone ?? 'UTC',
727            'language'     => $this->language ?? 'en',
728        ];
729    }
730
731    /**
732     * Get all available profile picture sizes
733     */
734    /**
735     * Get  profile picture sizes
736     */
737    public function getProfilePictureSizes(): array
738    {
739        if (! $this->profile_picture || ! $this->id) {
740            return [];
741        }
742
743        $sizes = [];
744        $profilePicturesPath = storage_path('app/public/profile-pictures');
745
746        if (is_dir($profilePicturesPath)) {
747            $files = glob($profilePicturesPath . "/profile_{$this->id}_*");
748
749            foreach ($files as $file) {
750                $filename = basename($file);
751                if (preg_match("/^profile_{$this->id}_.*_(\w+)\.webp$/", $filename, $matches)) {
752                    $sizeName = $matches[1];
753                    $sizes[$sizeName] = asset('storage/profile-pictures/' . $filename);
754                }
755            }
756        }
757
758        return $sizes;
759    }

765     * Get  profile picture url
766     */
767    public function getProfilePictureUrl(string $size = 'medium'): ?string
768    {
769        $sizes = $this->getProfilePictureSizes();
770
771        return $sizes[$size] ?? $this->getProfileDisplay()['picture_url'];
772    }
